Functional requirement chosen: FR-ST-5
Non-functional requirements are as follows:

SECURITY AND PRIVACY:
-The app should keep hidden from the user the back-end operations being performed between it and the hardware.
-Submitted information about organisation team members must be stored encrypted on the cloud.
-All inputs must be sanitized thoroughly to prevent malicious code injection.
-Rejected requests must have organisation team data securely and immediately deleted following rejection.
-contact details must be stored encrypted on the cloud.
-contact details must be securely and immediately deleted following rejected requests.
-A student who submits a request which is rejected must not be able to submit a new request until the following calendar month in order to prevent denial-of-service attacks.
-On boot, the app should check if an updated version is available and only function if its current version is the latest.
PERFORMANCE:
-it must be verified that all students whose information is given are members of the same university-specific student union.
-when a society is created, the content of the app should change to relfect this within 10 seconds.
-once the society has been approved, the organisation team must all be delivered a means to download and sign in to the Society Leader application within the next working day.
-Students who have their requests approved must be automatically granted member/subscriber status of their new society.
RELIABILITY:
-The app should provide its version number to the user for debugging reasons.
-students must not be able to start a society which already exists under their university-specific student union.
-Input fields for society description must be able to accept up to 5000 characters and refuse inputs longer than such.
-Input fields for names/contact details must be able to accept up to 500 characters and refuse inputs longer than such.
SCALABILITY:
-The app must be compatible with all major current-day smartphone operating systems.
-multiple students must be able to submit requests simultaneously. (>=10,000)
-an individual student must be able to subscribe to multiple societies simultaneously. (>250)
-multiple students must be able to subscribe to the same society. (>=10,000)
